{"word":"Ξ","slug":"Ξ","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<entryFree id=\"n71426\" key=\"*c\" type=\"main\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"entryFree\"> <orth extent=\"full\" lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"orth\">Ξ ξ,</orth> <orth extent=\"full\" lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"orth\">ξεῖ</orth> (q.v.), <gen lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"gen\">τό</gen>, <itype opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"itype\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ indecl.\">indecl.</a></itype>, fifteenth (later fourteenth) letter of most of the Eastern Greek alphabets, including the Ionic (later general Gr.) alphabet ; not used in Western Greek alphabets or in the native Attic alphabet ; in form and serial position (<bibl default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <title_ TEIform=\"title\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ IG\">IG</a></title_> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">14.2420</biblScope> </bibl>) it corresponds to the Semitic <sense id=\"n71426.0\" n=\"A\" level=\"1\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"sense\"> <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">samech</tr_> (a form of <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">s</tr_>), but has acquired the new value <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">ks</tr_> ; as numeral <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">ξ᾽</foreign> <abbr TEIform=\"abbr\">=</abbr> <bibl default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">60</biblScope></bibl>, but <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\"><num TEIform=\"num\">ξ᾽</num> </foreign> <abbr TEIform=\"abbr\">=</abbr> <bibl default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">60</biblScope></bibl>,<bibl default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">000</biblScope></bibl>.</sense> </entryFree>"}]}